    "note": "N3-pre.5 — dedicated copy of runtime-smoke/v1.json for smoke-testnet-faucet-to-block.sh. That smoke is the only one that boots with --state-dir + --proof-dedup-ledger, so its two /submit steps need distinct proof `bytes` (dedup hashes SHA-256(bytes) cross-pk); the shared v1.json fixture intentionally reuses one `bytes` value across steps (~60 other tests/scripts depend on that), so this smoke gets its own copy instead of mutating the shared one. Step 1's `bytes` is a structurally valid POFP-v1 package (same walk_package shape as v1.json's, decl_count=0) with its second literal expr bumped 1 -> 2, so it decodes cleanly under boole_core::validator and only differs in its SHA-256 dedup key."
